===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/bɪˈliːf/}}, {{SAMPA|/bI"li:f/}}
*{{audio|en-us-belief.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} < {{OE.}} ''[[lēafa]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# [[mental|Mental]] [[acceptance]] of a [[claim]] as [[truth]].
# {{countable}} Something [[believe]]d.
#: ''The ancient people have a '''belief''' in many deities.''
# {{uncountable}} The quality or state of [[believe|believing]].
#: ''My '''belief''' that it will rain tomorrow is strong.''
# {{uncountable}} [[religious|Religious]] [[faith]].
#: ''She often said it was her '''belief''' that carried her through the hard times.''
# {{in plural}} One's religious or [[moral]] [[convictions]].
#: ''I can't do that.  It's against my '''beliefs'''.''

